\chapter*{Disclaimers}

I wish that studies such as this weren’t necessary.
 They wouldn't be if we stopped considering pollination and many other natural processes as a “service” that non-human beings offer to humans for our system’s functioning.

We keep perceiving ourselves as damaging to the environment and not as part of it; we want to "protect" nature while all other life forms are objectified and enslaved to our system. Every moral limit is gone.
I believe there is a need to recognize that we don’t save or protect flora or fauna. Our way of existing, our production and our relationships have to take into account a collective and mutual care.


Once we recognize or just remember the interdependence of human and non-human life, without referring everything to profit it will be easier to build a different relationship with the environment and show solidarity with it \parencite{barcaForzeDiRiproduzione2024}.


